</paragraph>
<paragraph id="521136D9DA52126BDCA1FB8FFDF8FB5B" blockId="12.[178,1087,1119,1163]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">
T y p e m a t e r i a l: 
<typeStatus id="8D15887BDA52126BDDA1FB8FFE36FBA3" box="[434,507,1119,1139]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Holotype</typeStatus>
, Brit. O. Afrika, Kibwezi, 1907, Leg. Scheffler (MNHUB). 
<typeStatus id="8D15887BDA52126BDCCCFBA7FEE3FB5B" box="[223,302,1143,1163]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Paratype</typeStatus>
: 1, same origin (MNHUB).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1AB46552DA52126ADCA1FB4AFEC8FEDE" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1344" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343" type="description">
<paragraph id="521136D9DA52126BDCA1FB4AFE48FA4A" blockId="12.[178,1086,1177,1434]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Length 
<quantity id="95569B3CDA52126BDDE0FB49FDFAFB7F" box="[499,567,1177,1199]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
. Body shiny and yellowish-red, head and free aabdominal tergites free three and four reddish, antennae yellowish-red with the two basal antennomeres yellow, yellowish-red legs. Reticulation of the fore-body strong, that of the three basal free tergitgites evident, on the remaining free tergites superficial. Puncturation of head and pronotum fine and evident, that of the elytra double, with sparse strong punctures on a densely and finely punctuate background. Pronotum with two strong discal punctures. Fourth free tergite of the male with a feeble median carina, fifth with four strong granules in a transverse row, 
<figureCitation id="CA952A5CDA52126BDEE2FAB6FC8FFAAC" box="[753,834,1382,1404]" captionStart="Figs 57-64" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1417,1437]" captionTargetBox="[184,1059,230,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-6@29.[178,1085,524,820]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 57-64: Habitus, aedeagus in lateral and ventral views, spermatheca. (57-60) Zyras (Camonia) pugnax nov.sp.; (61-64) Zyras (Camonia) civilis nov.sp. Habitus scale bar Fig. 57: 6 mm; Fig. 61: 5.5 mm, other scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335323/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus 
<figureCitation id="CA952A5CDA52126BDFD0FAB6FBF4FAAC" box="[963,1081,1382,1404]" captionStart="Figs 57-64" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1417,1437]" captionTargetBox="[184,1059,230,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-6@29.[178,1085,524,820]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 57-64: Habitus, aedeagus in lateral and ventral views, spermatheca. (57-60) Zyras (Camonia) pugnax nov.sp.; (61-64) Zyras (Camonia) civilis nov.sp. Habitus scale bar Fig. 57: 6 mm; Fig. 61: 5.5 mm, other scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335323/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Figs 58-59</figureCitation>
, spermatheca 
<figureCitation id="CA952A5CDA52126BDD25FA54FE48FA4A" box="[310,389,1412,1434]" captionStart="Figs 57-64" captionStartId="29.[178,218,1417,1437]" captionTargetBox="[184,1059,230,1406]" captionTargetId="figure-6@29.[178,1085,524,820]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="Figs 57-64: Habitus, aedeagus in lateral and ventral views, spermatheca. (57-60) Zyras (Camonia) pugnax nov.sp.; (61-64) Zyras (Camonia) civilis nov.sp. Habitus scale bar Fig. 57: 6 mm; Fig. 61: 5.5 mm, other scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5335323" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5335323/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Fig. 60.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="521136D9DA52126BDCA1FA79FC69F9E4" blockId="12.[178,1085,1449,1588]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: In the secondary sexual characters of the first free abdominall tergite of the male, the new species is comparable to 
<emphasis id="60DAEACBDA52126BDF4BFA17FC08FA0C" box="[856,965,1479,1500]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="363F4B28DA52126BDFDFFA17FBF0FA0C" author="PACE R" box="[972,1085,1478,1500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343" pagination="1 - 34" refId="ref12388" refString="PACE R. (1988): Aleocharinae della Guinea-Bissau (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Boletim de la Sociedade portuguesa de Entomologia 99: 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1988">PACE 1988</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="2AB97649DA52126BDCE0FA33FE46FA29" box="[243,395,1507,1529]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Guinea-Bissau</collectingCountry>
. The new species differs from 
<emphasis id="60DAEACBDA52126BDEEEFA34FCBEFA29" box="[765,883,1508,1529]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
in the transverse pronotum, while that of 
<emphasis id="60DAEACBDA52126BDDA3F9D2FDD3F9C7" box="[432,542,1538,1559]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
is as long as wide. In ventral view, the apex of the aedeagus of the new species is very narrow, that of 
<emphasis id="60DAEACBDA52126BDEAFF9CFFCE5F9E4" box="[700,808,1567,1588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="1343">Z. vioensis</emphasis>
very broad.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="521136D9DA53126ADCA1FF0BFEC8FEDE" blockId="13.[178,1085,219,270]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1344">
E t y m o l o g y: The name of the new species derives from the Latin 
<emphasis id="60DAEACBDA53126ADFC4FF0BFBECFF20" box="[983,1057,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1344">pugnax</emphasis>
= warlike.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
